21st May 2022, I have been waiting to upload this picture since. 
Its been more than an year but I remember exactly what i felt when i saw @ratnapathakshah for the first time walking onto the set. 
I had sweaty palms, heart rate of a heart patient, excitement of a young child, expecting the worse to happen, but then we read a scene. I remember asking her can I please call you naani mumma? (that’s what i used to call my naani ) She pleasantly said yes! and all of a sudden things started feeling normal. 
She didn’t know what her pleasantly saying yes to me meant at that time, it made me feel i can do this.  That was my first validation on a film set. 
I have learned so so much just by observing her on set. Sharing screen with you will be one of the highlights of my life. ❤️
Thankyou @dudeja_sahaab and @parijat_joshi for creating Dhak Dhak. ❤️

PARINDI - Couldn’t come up with a better name, not my fault her partner’s name was NADAAN (also my fault but nonetheless) 
This woman demanded respect from the get go. 
Fierce. 
Her first confrontation with Caramel (Male orange cat almost 10) was a starring competition which ended up in a peace treaty. The balcony was now a shared space between a bird and cat. 
She learned how to open her own cage even tried teaching it to Naadan, he couldn’t so she would lift the door with her head and her partner would walk past it.
She turned to me once after doing that, almost saying “we don’t need to go in there, I can deal with them deadly things in air at night” 
Didn’t sleep in the cage after that, neither did naadan until he was attacked one day and left us. 
Love birds don’t tend to do well without their partners, they choose them for a lifetime.  PARINDI was young, she there was a chance that she would be open to a partner. 
She chose bhaijaan, his personality was exactly like Naadan. 

PARINDI- BHAIJAAN took some time but became a thing. 
We shifted houses as I third wheeled with them. 
Owned that place.

No matter the neighbours, she would sing first thing in the morning. Gallop over money plants, teach bhaijaan to do the same. Found a way to not get caught in human hands, would fly up to places one can’t reach. As others would pet bhaijaan she would wait for us to return him. 

Boss lady just kept bossing. 
Until the sun set. 

Lived so well, she’s making her absence feel. 

Rest in peace ❤️
(22/06/2024 - 18/02/2025)
